    "updated_at": "2025-03-14T14:18:38Z",
    "body": "Anybody know how to selectively disable the `git_*` modules when `jj root --ignore-working-copy` returns true, but leave `git_*` modules enabled otherwise?\n\nI'm adding the custom `jj` module from https://github.com/jj-vcs/jj/wiki/Starship but trying to figure out how to omit the git info in that case, because I'm still probably going to be working with a lot of plain git repos.\n\nEdit: I also posted about this here: https://github.com/starship/starship/discussions/4363#discussioncomment-12501692",
