    "body": "> @vergenzt  The 2nd example on the wiki has:\n> \n> ```\n> [git_branch]\n> disabled = true\n> \n> # re-enable git_branch as long as we're not in a jj repo\n> [custom.git_branch]\n> when = true\n> command = \"jj root >/dev/null 2>&1 || starship module git_branch\"\n> description = \"Only show git_branch if we're not in a jj repo\"\n> ```\n> \n> Although this seems a bit like a kludge to me. Regardless, does this not help?\n> \n> (and just noticed that `--ignore-working-copy` is missing for `jj root` commands, assuming this doesn't matter....)\n\nOh I totally missed that in the example. That should do it. Thanks!",
